==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obtusion
<hw>Ob*tu"sion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obtusio</ets>, from <ets>obtundere</ets> to blunt. See
<er>Obtund</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of making
obtuse or blunt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being dulled or blunted; <as>as, the
<ex>obtusion</ex> of the senses</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Harvey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obtusity</ent>⟦br⟧
